I’mHello, EDNA LEE Founder - 2021 Malaysia Book of Record Holder " The Biggest Mural by An Individual ” ABOUT ME Hello! I'm Edna Lee, a former National Basketball player in 2017, and started my journey as an artist began during the MCO in 2019. Currently, I proudly serve as the Director of Edna Creationz Sdn Bhd. I achieved a significant milestone by creating 'The Biggest Wall Mural by An Individual.' This remarkable achievement has been duly recognized by the Malaysia Book of Records, before graduating with a Diploma in Graphic Design from UCSI University in 2021 I firmly believe in the transformative power of art to bring people together and foster positive change in the world. I'm grateful for the opportunities I've had to share my passion with others, and I eagerly look forward to continuing to create meaningful " The Biggest Wall Mural by An Individual " and inspiring art in the years to come (40 days, 14.3m X 12.5m )

"BACK TO PROVENCE" L’Occitane En Provence Pavilions 2 Bukit Jalil, Malaysia L’Occitane “BIG little Things “ very first 3D environmental friendly mural project in Asia. L’Occitane is a brand from France ,Provence. the theme of the mural is based on brand story that more than only beauty care, their values touching lives around the world. This mural is made from eco friendly paints and 500 beauty empties of the 1,347,526 recyclable packaging (weighed at 61 tons!) collected from their BIG Little Things effort.

EDNAVERSE PROJECT OVERVIEW Ednaverse is a phygital custom shoe business that integrates the world of physical, hand-customized Nike Air Force 1s with NFTs. Goal: to empower sneaker enthusiasts to express their stories through both digital collectibles and real-world products. Decentralized Physical Infrastructure Networks (DePIN) - to enhance user engagement, create community-driven sneaker culture hubs, and provide lifestyle data tracking for customized sneaker experiences. NANA token - power Ednaverse's Web3 ecosystem, facilitating NFT minting, community-driven events, and rewards based on lifestyle data. @EDNAVERSE
